LAGOS  – A Nigerian flagged Motor Vessel, MV VIGEO ADEBOLA which was reported to be distressed midstream Federal Ocean Terminal Onne has been moved off the terminal. The vessel distressed due to operational error, according the Nigerian Maritime Administration and Safety Agency NIMASA has been moved to a better location clear away from the FOT Onne Channel. Osagie Edward, Assistant Director, Public Relations, NIMASA confirmed this in a statement made available to Daily Independent. Nedogas, NCDMB Commission 300 MMscfd Kwale Gas Gathering… Fidelity Bank GAIM 5 Promo: 10 More Customers Become… MV Vigeo Adebola had a port list on February 10, 2022 due to the fact that it received potable fresh water from a barge and it received all in the port fresh water tank. The vessel owners were able to correct the list on the February 13, 2022, by transferring some of the potable fresh water to the starboard side in order to have an even keel. Throughout this period, the Surveyors from NIMASA constantly monitored the vessel until the operation was completed and the vessel relocated. “It is noteworthy that at no point was the vessel having a negative metacentric height and vessel owners and captains are assured of safety of navigation on the Channel,” the statement added. Dr. Bashir Jamoh, Director General of NIMASA, has given the assurance that the Agency would continue to work with relevant authorities and stakeholders in ensuring the waterways and channels are safe for navigation. POLL “Let me use this opportunity to assure vessel owners, captains and all stakeholders, of the Agency’s commitment to its mandate, which includes maritime safety, geared towards safety of navigation of vessels in Nigerian territorial waters,” Jamoh said.